<h2 align="center">DEVIANT ARTIFACTS RESEARCH DIVISION</h2>
<h3 align="center">EOP-8009</h3>

<strong>Esoterica Operational Parameters</strong> #: EOP-8009

<strong>Esoterica Classification:</strong> Alternate-Omega (Temporal/Multiversal/Existential) <s>Exploratory</s> Strategic (see addendum)

<strong>Operational Parameters Summary:</strong> The object in question is a double-doorway, constructed of rowan wood and ash, three meters in height and the same in width, with a depth of two and a half centimeters. The object has hinges of brass and handles made with the same, with a latching locking mechanism constructed of cold iron. Sigils have been carved into the surface of the doors and their shared frame and filled with a mixture of cold iron and grave dirt taken from the final resting place of Magos T__ S__ M___. 

The exact nature of these sigils is not to be described in this document, except to state that they formulate a Level Ten Esoterica describing a conduit between our universe and the alternate universe initially discovered through Supernatural Phenomenon SPC-1764 ("Alternate Universe Supernatural Phenomenon Casefile”).

The object in question is inert unless activated. Activation procedures are restricted knowledge, accessible under permission from a First Circle Authority only to personnel who have undergone Level Ten Esoterica training, as well as certification for alternate universe exploration. Personnel must also receive an inoculation blessing immediately before transition, and may be subject to debriefing and exorcism to prevent transmission of disruptive/counterstatic memetics from the alternate dimension.

A warning: as with all alternate universes, there is a risk of cultural shock due to  incompatible social norms. Information isolation protocols are in effect. Maintain Information Security according to the strictures of The Unifier’s teachings (All Praise be to He).

<strong>Operational History:</strong> The impetus for the construction of this object was the discovery of the altered universe “SCP” as detailed in <a href="https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-1764">Supernatural Phenomenon Casefile SPC-1764 </a>, which will hereby be referred to as "the information anomaly." 

Although Esoteric Warfare responses were put into place following the discovery of Universe SCP, there was an understanding that a policy based on mutually assured destruction was undesirable due to the inability to engage in nuanced and controlled use of force to respond to less-than-apocalyptic threats. For this reason, research was carried out into the creation of a Esoterica Conduit by a DARD research team led by Master Actuarion I__ C__. 

Esoterica formulation was completed by the Fifth day of the Tenth Lunarium in the One Thousandth and Fourteenth Year of the United Empire (All Praise be to the Unifier). Esoterica passed review by the High Secretariat on the Tenth day of the same Lunarium and Year. Actual construction of the object in question was further delayed due to budgetary concerns until the following year. Construction began on the Second Day of the Second Lunarium of the One Thousandth and Fifteenth Year of the United Empire (All Praise be to the Unifier), and was completed on the Seventeenth Day of the Eighth Lunarium of the selfsame year.

<strong>Mission Statement:</strong> The purpose of this Esoterica is the exploration of Universe SCP, the cataloguing of the Supernatural Phenomena within, and the establishment of diplomatic relations with the native population.

Project Manager: Master Actuarion I__ C__
Project Priority: High.

<h6 align="right">So Let it Be Written, So Let it Be Done </h6>
<h3 align="right">IN THE UNIFIER'S NAME (All Praise be to He)</h3>


<br class="page-break">
