[[include :scp-wiki:component:pages
| medium=vintage-book
| contents=
<center><h2>The People of Universe SCP</h2></center>
<img src="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-8009/Otherworlder_Skel.png" alt="The Skeletal Remnants of an inhabitant of Universe SCP." height="500" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" position="top"></center>

Although outwardly similar to humanity, the SCPian is as alien to us as a serpent is from a fowl. Their fundamental essence of life is a twisted double-stranded ladder like ours, but the direction of the twist is reversed, and the fundamental components of each rung are as different as night and day. Of particular interest is the endcap structure, akin to our genetic memory structure: these portions of the essence appear to degrade over time, which must result in the complete decay of the structure within one hundred years of birth. This explains the horrifyingly short lifespan of the SCPian, and the wretched decay that plagues them after a few short decades of life.

The SCPian’s blood uses ferrum as its base, which is responsible for the unusual red color of their blood and the toxic properties of their flesh. Their internal organs are asymmetrical, like ours, but of opposite chirality. They possess analogues to most of our organs, including the cordia, pulmonia, and hepatia. They lack the oral venom gland and oculus tertium. Their bones are made of calx, making them hard, but brittle compared to ours. Their eyes lack a nightshine layer, giving them poor night vision. Internal structure of the ear is similar to ours, but the auricle is truncated and unarticulated, resulting in poor directional hearing. Their hands and feet have five digits of three joints each. Their skin ranges in tone from charcoal-black to a pallid pink. Their height averages a mere four cubis, their weight around ten petrela.

Although their physical form resembles ours, their metaphysics are closer to beast or vegetable than human. They emit no soul-fire: in fact, they will wither and die in the presence of that holy light. With the rare exception, SCPians are completely incapable of any sort of working: they have no gods, anchorum, or magi among them. The current belief is that SCPians are, in fact, soulless beasts without divine spark.

One might conclude that the SCPian represents no threat to us until one considers the nature of the reproductive systems. A mere decade and a half suffices for an infant to reach reproductive maturity, following which the female engages in a rapid cycle of monthly estrus. Males are perpetually fertile as well, requiring only a single donation of essence for the female to achieve conception. Witness the fact that despite their short lifespans, the reported SCPian population expands quickly, and will exceed one billion in a mere few centuries.

<br class="page-break">
<center><h2>SCPian Weaponry</h2></center>
<img src="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/scp-8009/alchemical_bow.png" alt="A diagram showing the internal workings of a SCPian Alchemical Bow." width="500" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" position="top">

The standard armament of the SCPian is the alchemical bow. Similar to the ring-bow, this weapon propels a projectile at high speed into the foe. Unlike the ring-bow, this weapon relies on an alchemical reaction caused by the ignition of a greyish powder which burns rapidly when exposed to fire. Through the burning of this powder, great quantities of a caustic gas are released, the pressure of which propels a small tapered projectile down a spiral-cut tube, imparting a spin which serves similar purpose to an arrow’s fletching, increasing its accuracy during flight.

<br class="page-break">
Without motive telekinetic force from the user to reload the weapon, the alchemical bow instead relies on a cunning system of moving linkages, tapping part of the energy from the projectile’s firing into a mechanism which automatically replaces the spent projectile with a fresh one held in a spring-loaded box attached to the weapon. Several of these spring-loaded boxes are carried by Otherlander soldiers, and through rapid removal and replacement of these boxes, the weapon can be returned to operation more swiftly than a ring-bow.

Should you encounter an alchemic bow, handle it with care, for it is forged of hot iron, and the projectiles themselves made of toxic plumbum with a copper casing. Should one be injured by an alchemic projectile, it is imperative that the toxic projectile be removed immediately, or the plumbum within will kill the victim’s soul within hours. Such is the treachery and cruelty of the soulless ones!

In addition to the alchemical bow, the SCPian wears garments of strong fiber, woven fine enough to halt an arrow in its tracks, reinforced with a lightweight porcelain plate cuirass over the chest and back. Many SCPian soldiers also carry a crude but serviceable steel knife: although incapable of penetrating starsilk garments, this weapon is still capable of cutting human throats. Do not approach a seemingly dead SCPian without first confirming that they are dead, for like a cunning beast, they are fond of feigning death to lure us to within knife range.

The following weapons are more rarely seen among the SCPians, who seem to issue them willy-nilly to individual soldiers. Most often seen is the tube-Arquebus, which hurls canisters filled with explosive or toxic alchemy through a similar mechanism to the alchemical bow. These weapons are often carried suspended under the alchemical bow, and appear to be carried by serjeants and chosen men. Target these individuals when possible. 

Another (more fearful) weapon is the explosive lance, which can penetrate dragonhide from a distance of many leagues. This weapon is characterized by the large launching tube braced on the shoulder, which contains the lance within. Like the alchemical bow, this weapon relies on the ignition of flammable powders to propel the projectile. Unlike the alchemical bow, the explosive lance’s projectiles contain a cunning mechanism which guides it to the target from a great distance: this device is capable of altering direction mid-flight, and can even strike from an advantageous angle to penetrate weaknesses in the target’s armor.
]]

