Let the words of my mouth sing the praise of a brave man. 

I sing to you of the death of Sirah Alamande Ulryc, Chevalier of the Unifier’s Knights. Son of Chevaliera Tsuling Ulryc, who forged his helix in her womb, bore him under her heart for a score of years, birthed him under the light of the three moons, raised him into manhood over ten-score years before he earned his name. Sirah Alamande, mighty in battle, master of the sword and lance, a wielder of sacred fire. Sirah Alamande, whose steed was Wotanna the Red and whose blade was Responsum, The Taker of Souls. Sirah Alamande, snow-white of hair and violet of eye, whose skin, it is said, shone like lapis lazuli, whose fair face and fairer words earned the hand and heart of Ofelya Mendal. Sirah Alamande, father to none, whose helix is now lost to us, lost at the hands of the vermin Otherworlders in the five thousand and seventh year of Our Unifier’s Empire.

Twenty-score and seventeen years had Sirah Alamande lived when he first stepped through the archway into the Otherworld. Though brave in battle and feared in war, Sirah Ulrich came as a messenger of peace, bearing a flag of truce stained with his own blood. Clad in the black of peace, his face hidden, he stained the titanium of his sabatons with the mud and filth of that foul place, but the corruption of the Otherworld’s earth could not corrupt his pure heart. Five-score were the Otherworlders who came to meet him, clad in poisonous iron, wielding spears and swords made of the same. Sirah Alamande feared them not, but called out to them, offering peace. 

Alas! Curses be upon the treacherous Otherlanders, whose hearts are as black as their garb! Poisoned arrows did they fire from their bows at the words of the brave Chevalier, and though their ferrum arrows could not pierce his armor, the foul vapors still sapped his strength. Three score blows did he bear and did not strike out against his foe, but instead repeated his plea for peace. In response, the Otherlanders did spur their four-legged steeds into battle, and lowered their lances. Sirah Alamande reached out with sacred fire to turn them away, but the ferum of their armor did turn away his magic, and the lances did pierce his body most cruelly.

Now comes the brave Capitaine, Michayla Teichts, a mighty hunter of men and beast alike. Dark of hair and eye was she, and skilled in blade and ring-bow. It was she whose arrows struck down the Queen of Foxes at the feast of blood and lights, she who held the line at the Battle of the Broken Bridge. Bravely she advanced through the doorway, leading three Rangers of her company. She shields herself from the foul bolts of the foe with pavise, but she cannot reach the fallen Chevalier. With regret do the Rangers place arrow to ring and fire. Swiftly did the Capitaine and her Rangers strike out against the foe, felling a score of them with their arrows, so that Eligos himself would nod approval at their war-craft. But the Otherlanders return fire with arrows tipped with poison, and the ferum vapors sap their strength.

Sorely wounded, Capitaine Teichts does order a full retreat. Bearing the fallen Sirah Ulryc upon their litter, she and her Rangers return to our world.

Thus ended the life of Sirah Alamande Ulryc. Weep for his death, for the broken heart of Lady Ofelya, for the children who will not be born and the millenia of life left unlived. Weep for the death of a brave man, and curses be upon the vermin who slew him.]]
